    <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
      <head altrender="biography" id="a2">BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE </head>
      <p>William Mangin acted as Field Director of the Vicos experimental station from
        1952-1953. He also was involved in the Barriadas in Lima and the Peace Corps in Peru
        and served as professor of anthropology at Syracuse University. His research
        interests included squatter settlements and mental health issues in Peru.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
      <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
      <p>Files, publications, clippings, field notes and field notebooks, photographs, and
        slides of Vicos and the Barriadas.</p>
    </scopecontent>
